# HTTP headers added by Cloudflare server when serving our pages and assets.
# See: https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/static-assets/headers/
#
# Most of these security headers were obtained by following the recommendations
# on https://securityheaders.com.
#
# You can run a security check on our deployed headers at any time using one
# of these links:
#   Staging: https://securityheaders.com/?q=staging.cccgainesville.org&followRedirects=on
#   Production: https://securityheaders.com/?q=cccgainesville.org&followRedirects=on

# Apply these headers to all paths served.
/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), display-capture=(), geolocation=(), magnetometer=(), gyroscope=(), accelerometer=()
#
# TODO: get rid of 'unsafe-inline', once Astro supports it. Can't currently, because
#       Astro's experimental CSP support doesn't currently play nice with the Accessible Starter theme.
#
# TODO: get rid of 'data:' as well, once we can use Astro's CSP support (see above).
#
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self' data: 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://secure.givelively.org https://fonts.googleapis.com; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://secure.givelively.org https://challenges.cloudflare.com; frame-src https://secure.givelively.org https://challenges.cloudflare.com; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'none'; manifest-src 'self' cccgainesville.cloudflareaccess.com; upgrade-insecure-requests
#
#
#
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-site
#  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp